---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import InfoPageHero from '../components/info/InfoPageHero.astro';
import { CONTACT_EMAIL } from '../lib/info-pages';
import { buildInfoPageSchema } from '../lib/seo/info-page-schema';
import { formatEditorialDate } from '../lib/editorial';
import '../styles/info-pages.css';

const title = 'Privacy Policy';
const description =
  'Read the Tire Reference privacy policy to understand what information may be collected, how it is used, and your available privacy choices.';

const schema = buildInfoPageSchema(title, description, '/privacy-policy/', 'Privacy Policy');
const updated = formatEditorialDate();
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical="/privacy-policy/" schema={schema}>
  <div class="info-page">
    <div class="info-shell info-shell--narrow">
      <InfoPageHero
        title="Privacy Policy"
        lead="This policy explains what information Tire Reference may collect when you use our website, how we use it, and the choices available to you."
      />

      <article class="info-legal">
        <h2>Who operates this website</h2>
        <p>
          Tire Reference is an independently operated informational website. Legal, privacy, and
          data enquiries may be sent through the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a> or to{' '}
          <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>Information we collect</h2>
        <p>
          Tire Reference does not require an account. When you use the contact or issue-report
          forms, the information you enter is used to prepare an email in your own email client.
          The website does not receive that information unless you send the email. If you do, we
          receive the sender details, subject, message, and any other information you choose to
          include.
        </p>
        <p>
          Calculator inputs are processed to provide results and do not require vehicle ownership
          details, VINs, or purchase history. Hosting and security providers may process limited
          technical data, such as IP address, browser information, requested pages, and timestamps,
          to deliver and protect the website.
        </p>

        <h2>Cookies and analytics</h2>
        <p>
          The calculators do not require advertising or affiliate cookies. Tire Reference may use
          limited analytics to understand aggregate traffic and improve reliability. Where Google
          Analytics is active, Google may process device and usage information and may use cookies
          or similar technologies under its own privacy terms.
        </p>
        <p>
          You can limit cookies through your browser settings and use any controls provided by the
          analytics provider. Blocking non-essential cookies does not prevent access to the
          calculators.
        </p>

        <h2>Data retention</h2>
        <p>
          Messages and support enquiries are retained only for as long as reasonably necessary to
          respond, maintain appropriate records, prevent abuse, and meet applicable legal
          obligations. Technical logs and analytics information are retained according to
          operational need and the applicable service provider&apos;s settings, then deleted,
          aggregated, or anonymized where appropriate.
        </p>

        <h2>Advertising</h2>
        <p>
          Tire Reference does not currently display third-party advertising.
        </p>

        <h2>Affiliate links</h2>
        <p>
          Tire Reference does not currently use affiliate links or participate in affiliate
          programs.
        </p>

        <h2>Third-party services</h2>
        <p>
          Service providers may process limited information where needed to host, secure, and
          measure the website or deliver email. Their handling of information is also governed by
          their own terms and privacy policies.
        </p>
        <p>
          Tire Reference may link to external websites, including manufacturer documentation.
          External websites control their own privacy practices.
        </p>

        <h2>How information is used</h2>
        <p>We use collected information to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Operate, maintain, and secure Tire Reference</li>
          <li>Respond to questions, feedback, and support requests</li>
          <li>Improve calculators, content, and site performance</li>
          <li>Detect abuse, fraud, or technical issues</li>
          <li>Comply with applicable legal obligations</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not sell your personal information for money. See the CCPA section below for California-specific rights regarding &quot;sale&quot; and &quot;sharing&quot; as defined by California law.
        </p>

        <h2>Your privacy rights</h2>
        <p>
          Depending on where you live, you may have rights to request access to, correction of, or
          deletion of personal information, to object to or restrict certain processing, or to
          withdraw consent where consent applies.
        </p>
        <p>
          To make a privacy request, use the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a> or email{' '}
          <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>. We may request information
          reasonably necessary to verify and respond to the request. You may also have the right to
          contact your local privacy or data-protection authority.
        </p>
        <p>
          Where applicable, processing may be based on consent, legitimate interests in operating
          and securing the website, responding to requests, or compliance with legal obligations.
        </p>

        <h2>Sale or sharing of personal information</h2>
        <p>
          Tire Reference does not sell personal information for money and does not currently use
          third-party advertising or affiliate tracking. If applicable law treats an active
          analytics service as a sale or sharing, you may contact us to exercise any available
          opt-out right.
        </p>

        <h2>Data security</h2>
        <p>
          We implement reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational measures designed to protect information against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. No method of transmission over the internet is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For privacy-related questions or requests, email{' '}
          <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a> or visit the{' '}
          <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>.
        </p>
      </article>

      <p class="info-updated">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
